<font color="#FF0000">POWS ON HOME SOIL</font><br>
<tt>Tue Oct 28 21:21:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Yes, this page brought me to tears as do most Vietnam Vet sites.  I can identify with Beth so much.  Talk with someone, but who? I married a Vietnam Veteran when I was 19 years old, 26 years ago.  Our marriage lasted 7 years but I still carry the pain and feel like I abandoned a very good man which you basically described to a 'T'.  We went to AA, we went to church counselors, nothing helped.  BUT neither of us knew what was wrong!!!!  My exhusband was just diagnosed with PTSD!!! Almost 30 years after he came home from Vietnam.  I am very bitter towards our government for not helping OUR BOYS who courageously devoted their childhoods to the meatgrinder war, and yes it was a WAR, I don't care how it was labeled.  After reading this page I see POWs walking on home soil. Prisoners of War walking on US soil.  What a burden. 
<p><code>-- sherric@televar.com  (Sherri Camacho) </code><p>


